what are you?

17:04.201 --> 17:06.102
Six-five.
Six... five!

17:06.103 --> 17:07.368
Wow, so is he!

17:07.371 --> 17:08.637
I love it!
Tell me more.

17:08.638 --> 17:11.007
Oh, well, what
can I say?

17:11.008 --> 17:12.842
I mean, every man wants him.

17:12.843 --> 17:14.542
Every woman wants to be him.

17:14.545 --> 17:17.112
Oh, I must tell you I'm
obsessed with this character.

17:17.114 --> 17:19.415
Oh, well, get in line!
So am I.

17:19.415 --> 17:22.451
Yeah, I mean, the...
the problem is that,

17:22.452 --> 17:25.087
you know, with this
time travel element,

17:25.088 --> 17:29.692
she leaves and-and he gets
left behind really early on.

17:29.693 --> 17:32.093
And... well, I'm just

17:32.095 --> 17:34.629
too stupid to figure out
a way to fix it, so...

17:36.332 --> 17:38.600
(quietly): I'm sorry.

17:46.042 --> 17:47.610
I'm going to pitch
something crazy.

17:47.611 --> 17:48.744
Oh.

17:48.745 --> 17:52.348
How about we beef up this
well-endowed gentleman

17:52.349 --> 17:56.851
and, uh, just pull back on the
whole time travel element?

17:57.686 --> 17:59.088
Ooh, aah!
(imitates explosion)

17:59.089 --> 18:00.322
Right?
Wow!

18:00.323 --> 18:01.690
Uh...

18:01.691 --> 18:03.859
tha-that's brilliant!

18:03.860 --> 18:05.361
Oh, my... I mean, I...

18:05.362 --> 18:06.829
Just going off of what you said,

18:06.830 --> 18:09.865
now I'm thinking... can we
just take that whole time...

18:09.866 --> 18:12.701
